# Unit Tests for <B34>

The constant function **<B34>** always returns 34 for any integer input. Below is a comprehensive test suite to verify this behavior.

```python
def B34(x):
    return 34

def test_B34():
    """Comprehensive test suite for <B34> function."""

    # Test with positive integers
    assert B34(1) == 34, "Failed for input 1"
    assert B34(100) == 34, "Failed for input 100"
    assert B34(7) == 34, "Failed for input 7"

    # Test with negative integers
    assert B34(-1) == 34, "Failed for input -1"
    assert B34(-50) == 34, "Failed for input -50"
    assert B34(-999) == 34, "Failed for input -999"

    # Test with zero
    assert B34(0) == 34, "Failed for input 0"

    # Test consistency
    assert B34(42) == B34(42), "Function is not consistent"

    # Test that different inputs yield same output
    assert B34(3) == B34(8), "Different inputs should yield same output"

    print("All tests passed for <B34>!")

test_B34()
```

